XXII. These stories give eredibility to Demo- critus also, who tells a tale of Thoas in Arcadia being saved by a snake. When a boy he had fed it and made a great pet of it, and his parent being afraid of the snake's nature and size had taken it away into an uninhabited region, where it recognized Thoas’s voice and came to his reseue when he was entrapped by an ambush of brigands.
